import re
train["Title"] = train["Name"].apply(lambda x: re.search(' ([A-Za-z]+)\.',x).group(1))
title_mapping = {"Mr": 1, "Miss": 2, "Mrs": 3, "Master": 4, "Dr": 5, "Rev": 6, "Major": 7, "Col": 7, "Mlle": 2, "Mme": 3,"Don": 9,"Dona": 9, "Lady": 10, "Countess": 10, "Jonkheer": 10, "Sir": 9, "Capt": 7, "Ms": 2}

# Title
train["NewTitle"] = train.loc[:,'Title'].map(title_mapping)

# SibSpParch
train["FamilySize"] = train["SibSp"] + train["Parch"] + 1

# FamilySize
train["FamilySize"] = pd.cut(train["FamilySize"], bins=[0,1,4,20], labels=[0,1,2])

# NameName
train["NameLength"] = train["Name"].apply(lambda x: len(x))

train["Embarked"] = pd.Categorical(train.Embarked).codes

# Sex
train = pd.concat([train,pd.get_dummies(train['Sex'])],axis=1)

In [1048]:
# 
child_age = 14
def get_person(passenger):
    age, sex = passenger
    if (age < child_age):
        return 'child'
    elif (sex == 'female'):
        return 'female_adult'
    else:
        return 'male_adult'

In [1051]:
table_ticket = pd.DataFrame(train["Ticket"].value_counts())
table_ticket.rename(columns={'Ticket':'Ticket_Numbers'}, inplace=True)
table_ticket['Ticket_dead_women'] = train.Ticket[(train.female_adult == 1.0) 
                                    & (train.Survived == 0.0) 
                                    & ((train.Parch > 0) | (train.SibSp > 0))].value_counts()

table_ticket['Ticket_dead_women'] = table_ticket['Ticket_dead_women'].fillna(0)
table_ticket['Ticket_dead_women'][table_ticket['Ticket_dead_women'] > 0] = 1.0

table_ticket['Ticket_surviving_men'] = train.Ticket[(train.male_adult == 1.0) 
                                    & (train.Survived == 1.0) 
                                    & ((train.Parch > 0) | (train.SibSp > 0))].value_counts()

table_ticket['Ticket_surviving_men'] = table_ticket['Ticket_surviving_men'].fillna(0)
table_ticket['Ticket_surviving_men'][table_ticket['Ticket_surviving_men'] > 0] = 1.0 

# Ticket
table_ticket["Ticket_Id"] = pd.Categorical(table_ticket.index).codes

table_ticket["Ticket_Id"][table_ticket["Ticket_Numbers"] < 3 ] = -1
# Ticket
table_ticket["Ticket_Numbers"] = pd.cut(table_ticket["Ticket_Numbers"], bins=[0,1,4,20], labels=[0,1,2])

train = pd.merge(train, table_ticket, left_on="Ticket",right_index=True, how='left', sort=False)

In [1052]:
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier, ExtraTreesRegressor

classers = ['Fare','Parch','Pclass','SibSp','NewTitle', 
            'female','male', 'Embarked', 'FamilySize', 'NameLength','Ticket_Numbers','Ticket_Id']
etr = ExtraTreesRegressor(n_estimators=200,random_state=0)
X_train = train[classers][train['Age'].notnull()]
Y_train = train['Age'][train['Age'].notnull()]
X_test = train[classers][train['Age'].isnull()]

etr.fit(X_train.as_matrix(),np.ravel(Y_train))
age_preds = etr.predict(X_test.as_matrix())
train['Age'][train['Age'].isnull()] = age_preds

In [1063]:
# 
child_age = 14
def get_person(passenger):
    age, sex = passenger
    if (age < child_age):
        return 'child'
    elif (sex == 'female'):
        return 'female_adult'
    else:
        return 'male_adult'

table_ticket = pd.DataFrame(test["Ticket"].value_counts())
table_ticket.rename(columns={'Ticket':'Ticket_Numbers'}, inplace=True)
table_ticket['Ticket_dead_women'] = test.Ticket[(test.female_adult == 1.0) 
                                    & (test.Survived == 0.0) 
                                    & ((test.Parch > 0) | (test.SibSp > 0))].value_counts()

table_ticket['Ticket_dead_women'] = table_ticket['Ticket_dead_women'].fillna(0)
table_ticket['Ticket_dead_women'][table_ticket['Ticket_dead_women'] > 0] = 1.0

table_ticket['Ticket_surviving_men'] = test.Ticket[(test.male_adult == 1.0) 
                                    & (test.Survived == 1.0) 
                                    & ((test.Parch > 0) | (test.SibSp > 0))].value_counts()

table_ticket['Ticket_surviving_men'] = table_ticket['Ticket_surviving_men'].fillna(0)
table_ticket['Ticket_surviving_men'][table_ticket['Ticket_surviving_men'] > 0] = 1.0 

# Ticket
table_ticket["Ticket_Id"] = pd.Categorical(table_ticket.index).codes

table_ticket["Ticket_Id"][table_ticket["Ticket_Numbers"] < 3 ] = -1
# Ticket

test = pd.merge(test, table_ticket, left_on="Ticket",right_index=True, how='left', sort=False)

from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier, ExtraTreesRegressor
classers = ['Fare','Parch','Pclass','SibSp','NewTitle', 
            'female','male', 'Embarked', 'FamilySize', 'NameLength','Ticket_Numbers','Ticket_Id']

etr = ExtraTreesRegressor(n_estimators=200,random_state=0)
X_train = test[classers][test['Age'].notnull()]
Y_train = test['Age'][test['Age'].notnull()]
X_test = test[classers][test['Age'].isnull()]

etr.fit(X_train.as_matrix(),np.ravel(Y_train))
age_preds = etr.predict(X_test.as_matrix())
test['Age'][test['Age'].isnull()] = age_preds

from sklearn.feature_selection import SelectKBest, f_classif,chi2

target = train["Survived"].values
features= ['female','male','Age','male_adult','female_adult', 'child','NewTitle',
           'Pclass','Ticket_Id','NameLength','NewCabin', 'SibSp', 'Parch',
           'Fare','Embarked','Ticket_Numbers','FamilySize',
           'Ticket_dead_women','Ticket_surviving_men','isAlone'
          ]

X_train = train.copy()
X_test = test.copy()

selector = SelectKBest(f_classif, k=len(features))
selector.fit(train[features], target)
scores = -np.log10(selector.pvalues_)
indices = np.argsort(scores)[::-1]
print("Features importance :")
for f in range(len(scores)):
    print("%0.2f %s" % (scores[indices[f]],features[indices[f]]))

from sklearn import cross_validation

rfc = RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=3000, min_samples_split=4, class_weight={0:0.745,1:0.255})
# rfc = AdaBoostClassifier(n_estimators=3000, learning_rate=0.1, random_state=1)

# 
kf = cross_validation.KFold(train.shape[0], n_folds=3, random_state=1)

scores = cross_validation.cross_val_score(rfc, train[features_selected], target, cv=kf)
print("Accuracy: %0.3f (+/- %0.2f) [%s]" % (scores.mean()*100, scores.std()*100, 'RFC Cross Validation'))
rfc.fit(train[features_selected], target)
score = rfc.score(train[features_selected], target)
print("Accuracy: %0.3f            [%s]" % (score*100, 'RFC full test'))
importances = rfc.feature_importances_
indices = np.argsort(importances)[::-1]
for f in range(len(features_selected)):
    print("%d. feature %d (%f) %s" % (f + 1, indices[f]+1, importances[indices[f]]*100, features_selected[indices[f]]))
